	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: VRC-VI multicart</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In recent times, they started packaging reduced numbers of gates, usually in surface-mount: e.g. 74AHC1G32, 74AHC2G32. Otherwise, all through-hole variants of the 74'32 always came with 4 gates. After that, anything except 74(no letter), 74F, and 74S (1, 0.6, and 1mA inlet current respectively) should be feasible. (74AS is 0.1mA, and everything else is lower). Avoid 3V-and-lower logic. ( <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/7400_series">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/7400_series</a><!-- m --> )<br /><br />It looks like he's using two OR gates, so I don't think there's a great alternative here. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Point-to-point_construction#.22Dead_bug.22_construction" class="postlink">Dead-bugging SMT</a> isn't that bad, though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


